ꜱᴋᴇʟ 2024-05-27 12:44 AM
well there are a few ways. socially and medically can be two different ways. socially, its very much like the first time you've told anyone you are trans. think a trans woman wearing skirts and makeup for the first time, or a trans man trying on men's clothes. this is usually what you do first. sometimes, trans people go on to transition medically, but not always! however they want to transition is up to them. but i've chosen, and many trans people choose, to transition medically, which involes injecting testosterone or estrogen. this involves going through more or less a second puberty to actually "physically" look like one's real gender.
